titlestmt.titleproper: Rockefeller Foundation records, Officers' Actions, RG 16
A Guide to the Rockefeller Foundation records, Officers' Actions, RG 16 FA474

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace on 2016-11-03 11:11:53 -0400.

did.unittitle: Rockefeller Foundation records, Officers' Actions, RG 16
did.physdesc: 31 standard record storage boxes. Accession 1: Boxes 1-12. Acession 2: Boxes 1-15, 15A, 16, 17, 18.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use note
userestrict.p: Rockefeller Foundation retains title, copyright and literary and intellectual property rights to the records, in so far as it holds them.
RAC has authority to grant permission to publish for scholarly purposes.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation note
prefercite.p: Information regarding the Rockefeller Archive Center's preferred elements and forms of citation can be found at http://www.rockarch.org/research/citations.php

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access note
accessrestrict.p: Records more than 20 years old are open for research with select materials restricted as noted. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC. Researchers interested in accessing digital media (floppy disks, CDs, DVDs, etc.) or audiovisual material (audio cassettes, VHS, etc.) in this collection must use an access surrogate. The original items may not be accessed because of preservation concerns. To request an access surrogate be made, or if you are unsure if there is an access surrogate, please contact an archivist.

processinfo.head: Processing Information note
processinfo.p: Records have received basic level 1 processing to establish initial intellectual and physical control of the holdings. Materials physically remain as received, in original record cartons and folders.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Types of records include: grant and fellowship material.
